TITLE: Basic Field Validation in Elementor Forms
DESCRIPTION: Implementation of basic field validation method that checks if a number is positive. The validation method runs when the form is submitted and adds error messages using the ajax handler if validation fails.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elementor/elementor-developers-docs/blob/master/src/form-fields/field-validation.md#2025-04-20_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
class Elementor_Test_Field extends \ElementorPro\Modules\Forms\Fields\Field_Base {

	public function validation( $field, $record, $ajax_handler ): void {

		if ( empty( $field['value'] ) ) {
			return;
		}

		if ( (int) $field['value'] > 0 ) {
			$ajax_handler->add_error(
				$field['id'],
				esc_html__( 'The field must contain a positive number.', 'textdomain' )
			);
		}

