TITLE: Removing Widget Action from Context Menu in Elementor
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to remove a 'widget-action' from the 'custom-widget-actions' group in the widget context menu. It uses the 'elements/context-menu/groups' filter hook to find and remove the target action by name.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elementor/elementor-developers-docs/blob/master/src/context-menu/remove-action.md#2025-04-20_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
elementor.hooks.addFilter( 'elements/context-menu/groups', ( customGroups, elementType ) => {

	if ( 'widget' === elementType ) {
		customGroups.forEach( ( group ) => {
			if ( 'custom-widget-actions' === group.name ) {
				const actionIndex = group.actions.findIndex( ( action ) => 'widget-action' === action.name );
				if ( actionIndex > -1 ) {
					group.actions.splice( actionIndex, 1 );
				}
			}
		} );
	}

	return customGroups;

} );
```

