TITLE: Adding CSS Rule with Unique Elementor Selector
DESCRIPTION: This function demonstrates how to add a CSS rule with a unique Elementor selector. It uses theme configuration functions to get dynamic values for width and height, and applies them to the element's unique selector.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elementor/elementor-developers-docs/blob/master/src/hooks/parse-element-css.md#2025-04-20_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: PHP
CODE:
```
/**
 * parse element CSS.
 *
 * @since 1.0.0
 * @param \Elementor\Core\Files\CSS\Post $post_css_file The post CSS file instance.
 * @param \Elementor\Element_Base        $element       The element instance.
 */
function add_custom_rules_to_css_file( $post_css_file, $element ) {

	$item_width = some_get_theme_config_function( 'item_width' );
	$item_height = some_get_theme_config_function( 'item_height' );

	$post_css_file->get_stylesheet()->add_rules(
		$element->get_unique_selector(),
		[
			'width' => $item_width . 'px',
			'height' => $item_height . 'px',
		]
	);

}
add_action(	'elementor/element/parse_css', 'add_custom_rules_to_css_file', 10, 2 );
```

