TITLE: Implementing Function Deprecation in PHP
DESCRIPTION: Example showing how to properly deprecate a function by creating a new method while maintaining backward compatibility with the old one. Includes the deprecation notice using Plugin::$instance->modules_manager->get_modules( 'dev-tools' )->deprecation->deprecated_function().
SOURCE: https://github.com/elementor/elementor-developers-docs/blob/master/src/deprecations/deprecated-function.md#2025-04-20_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
use Elementor\Plugin;

class Items {

	function register( $item_instance ): void {
		/* ... */
	}

	function add_item( $item_instance ): void {
		// Deprecation handler
		Plugin::$instance->modules_manager->get_modules( 'dev-tools' )->deprecation->deprecated_function(
			'add_item()',
			'3.5.0',
			'register()'
		);

		// Backwards compatibility
		$this->register( $item_instance );
	}

}
```

