TITLE: Adding a Color Control to Elementor Widget PHP
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to implement a color control in an Elementor widget. It shows how to set a label and default color value for the control.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elementor/elementor-developers-docs/blob/master/src/editor-controls/regular-control.md#2025-04-20_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
class Elementor_Test_Widget extends \Elementor\Widget_Base {

	protected function register_controls(): void {

		$this->start_controls_section(
			'content_section',
			[
				'label' => esc_html__( 'Content', 'textdomain' ),
				'tab' => \Elementor\Controls_Manager::TAB_CONTENT,
			]
		);

		$this->add_control(
			'text_color',
			[
				'type' => \Elementor\Controls_Manager::COLOR,
				'label' => esc_html__( 'Text Color', 'textdomain' ),
				'default' => '#fefefe',
			]
		);

		$this->end_controls_section();

	}

}
```

