TITLE: Registering Controls for Custom Action in Elementor Pro
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the basic structure for registering controls in a custom action class. The register_settings_section() method is used to add controls to the form widget.
SOURCE: https://github.com/elementor/elementor-developers-docs/blob/master/src/form-actions/action-controls.md#2025-04-20_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
class Elementor_Test_Action extends \ElementorPro\Modules\Forms\Classes\Action_Base {

	protected function register_settings_section( $widget ): void {

		$widget->start_controls_section();

		$widget->add_control();

		$widget->add_control();

		$widget->add_control();

		$widget->end_controls_section();

	}

}
```

